1. A design pattern that is specifically concerned with communication between object as the program is running is called?
Ans: Behavioral Pattern

2. A singleton design pattern _____.
Ans:
- is needed when we want to create one object of a class and no more instances of that class
- is the ability to create a class that can only have one instance
- is the ability to create a class that provides just one way to get to it

3. The Momento object is what gets created when the CareTaker class requests that
  the Originator class save itself. The Memento object details the important parts
  of the Originator class and the information needed to return to a particular state.
Ans: true
